.TH "adxl_decode" 9 "adxl_decode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
adxl_decode \- ask BIOS to decode a system address to memory address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" adxl_decode
.BI "(u64 addr "  ","
.BI "u64 component_values[] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
the address to decode
.IP "component_values" 12
pointer to array of values for each component
Returns 0 on success, negative error code otherwise
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The index of each value returned in the array matches the index of
each component name returned by \fBadxl_get_component_names\fP.
Components that are not defined for this address translation (e.g.
mirror channel number for a non-mirrored address) are set to ~0ull.
